Package com.rb.nonbiz.text

Interface HasHumanReadableLabel

All Known Implementing Classes:
InstrumentType, InstrumentType.EtfInstrumentType, InstrumentType.MutualFundInstrumentType, InstrumentType.StockInstrumentType, InstrumentType.StructuredProductInstrumentType, ItemWithLabel, N_aryFunction, N_aryOperator, NPlusOneAryFunction, NPlusOneAryPredicate, RBNumericFunction, RBNumericFunctionThatHandlesMissingValues, RBStringToNumericFunctionThatHandlesMissingValues, UnitFractionFunction
public interface HasHumanReadableLabel
Sometimes you want some objects to have a human-readable label that's not quite the same as what would show in toString(). E.g. a timeseries could be labeled "monthly housing returns".
